# Cursor Rules for Untime Project

## General Guidelines
- Focus on code quality and functionality
- Write clear, maintainable code
- Follow existing code style and patterns
- Add appropriate comments for complex logic

## Git Behavior
- Do NOT automatically commit and push changes after every request
- Only commit and push when explicitly requested by the user
- Always ask for confirmation before committing changes
- Use descriptive commit messages that explain the changes made

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow Svelte 5 conventions and syntax
- Maintain consistent indentation and formatting
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## Testing
- Consider edge cases and error handling
- Test functionality thoroughly before suggesting commits
- Ensure changes work across different devices and browsers

## Documentation
- Update comments when modifying complex logic
- Explain the purpose of new features or fixes
- Keep README and other documentation up to date when relevant 
